The paper discusses the incorporation of eScholarship into the Data Web, which involves the aggregation and description of web resources. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cyberinfrastructure (cs.CY), social networks (cs.SI), and databases (cs.DB). However, since the paper focuses on the technical aspects of aggregating and describing web resources, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
